    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The husband and father should consider all these things lest the wife and mother of his children be overtaxed and thus overwhelmed with despondency. He should see to it that the mother of his children is not placed in a position where she cannot possibly do justice to her numerous little ones, so that they have to come up without proper training.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">4<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 6-24-1890\" data-link=\"821.10514\">The Review and Herald, June 24, 1890</span>.</span></a></sup>",
